results.name: Expansion of c(q^2)^2 / (c(q) * c(q^6)) in powers of q where c() is a cubic AGM theta function.
link: G. C. Greubel, Table of n, a(n) for n = -1..1000
formula: Expansion of eta(q) * eta(q^6)^7 / (eta(q^2)^2 * eta(q^3)^3 * eta(q^18)^3) in powers of q.
mathematica: eta[x_] := x^(1/24)*QPochhammer[x]; A182033[n_] := SeriesCoefficient[ eta[q]*eta[q^6]^7/(eta[q^2]^2*eta[q^3]^3*eta[q^18]^3 ), {q, 0, n}]; Table[A182033[n], {n, -1, 50}] (* _G. C. Greubel_, Aug 18 2017 *)
program: (PARI) {a(n) = local(A); if( n<-1, 0, n++; A = x * O(x^n); polcoeff( eta(x + A) * eta(x^6 + A)^7 / (eta(x^2 + A)^2 * eta(x^3 + A)^3 * eta(x^18 + A)^3), n))}
